{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620328","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620328"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:40:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:40:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16623"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16623","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16623"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.14,0.05,0.14,0.68]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9314"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68673"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9314","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9314"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16623"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54130"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5319"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22087"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23026"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68673","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68673"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAnastrozole can be used in the treatment of a number of different cancers.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"For which one of the following would it be most effective?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Advanced uterine leiomyosarcoma","Hormone-dependent ovarian cancer","Metastatic endometrial cancer","Oestrogen receptor-negative breast cancer","Oestrogen receptor-positive breast cancer"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary indication for anastrozole is \u003Cstrong\u003Etreatment of oestrogen receptor-positive breast cancer\u003C/strong\u003E in postmenopausal women. It works by blocking the aromatase enzyme, reducing oestrogen production in peripheral tissues.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreatment of oestrogen receptor-negative breast cancer\u003C/strong\u003E - Hormonal therapies like anastrozole are ineffective in oestrogen receptor-negative disease\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreatment of metastatic endometrial cancer\u003C/strong\u003E - While some endometrial cancers are hormone-responsive, aromatase inhibitors are not first-line therapy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreatment of hormone-dependent ovarian cancer\u003C/strong\u003E - Although some ovarian cancers express hormone receptors, evidence for aromatase inhibitor use is limited\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreatment of advanced uterine leiomyosarcoma\u003C/strong\u003E - Aromatase inhibitors have limited efficacy in uterine sarcomas\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnastrozole is specifically used in postmenopausal women because after menopause, oestrogen is primarily produced in peripheral tissues rather than the ovaries. Regular bone mineral density monitoring is required during treatment due to increased fracture risk.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Anastrozole is primarily used to treat oestrogen receptor-positive breast cancer in postmenopausal women.","Aromatase inhibitors are contraindicated in premenopausal women as they cannot effectively suppress ovarian oestrogen production.","Monitoring bone mineral density is important during anastrozole therapy due to increased risk of osteoporosis."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54130"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16623"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54130","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/54130"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-10T09:58:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-10T09:58:55+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9314"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68673"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data